<br>
Chain cast 51 earth, burnout then cadeau... if you have velious pants do DS first then pants, unless mob is rooted when new pet pops up. Keep inventory opened for pet hotkeys while casting. If you do /pet get lost and slixin is rooted.. back off a bit and BO3 pants your pet, press F8 once you start casting and prepare to hotkey send pet when root breaks. Recast pets at 20-25% health... lower is risky but more efficient if you're confident. Also recommend other's hits on... if you see your pet sux0r then you know new pet at 25% or so, if he's hitting for 58 or 60 you know you can cut it a little closer. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~~~~Krilen !~~~~</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urpzmaj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RP Zmaj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(3/13/02 5:26:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=999.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/rpzmaj/ez_zmaj WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Solo Slixin Klex ?</span><hr size=1> Well I was out in BW tonight (or last night since it's afte rmidnight) as a 52 Mage you CAN solo him.  I stood on the back column away from Slixen by the comet/lavapit place.  Buffed up 51 Earth pet with BO3, 2 Symbol Daggers, and Summoned plate.  Summoned two Lev rings, DSed pet and medded to full.  Hit the Jbooties then sent the pet after Slixen and fired off a Bolt of Lava while pet was running to him.  Soon as my recast was done I started another bolt.  Depending on if Pet root held or not this actually went off or I had to turn tail and run.  Run toward the North (I think, long ways the other side of the creator).  Slixen runs slower then you'd imagine.  Every few seconds do a 360 and see if the pet has him rooted.  If he does fire off a bolt.  If he doesn't continue running.  Make sure you dodge all the other mobs around.  Soloing him 3 times I only had one add and he dissapeared somewhere.  Once you hit half mana sit down and med (Use 3rd person view to watch for mobs) and wait for Slixen to catch you or kill pet and come after you.  If he kills the pet summon another and send it out after him and repeat the running nuke.  Took 2 pets and a full bar of mana to kill him with 209 Int and a decent number of +mana items.  None of them dropped the Dirt, however a group was kind enough to let me pull to them and we did that twice (no dirt) on the 3rd time it got KSed while I was pulling and Woot! he dropped the Dirt and the 3 that killed him told me to loot since it was my pull and they had no mages. <p><p align="center"><a href="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/zmaj/index.html"><img border="0" src="http://members.aol.com/rpzmaj/kofkash.jpg" width="528" height="237"></a></p>

